xyz.fsgek.common.cache

Interface GekCache<K,V>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - key type
    V - value type

    @ThreadSafe
public interface GekCache<K,V>
    Cache interface, provides get/compute/put/contains/expire/remove/clear/clean methods which perform like ConcurrentHashMap. Implementations should be thread-safe, this is defined in this interface.

    This cache supports set different expiration for each entry, and null value is permitted. However, default implementation is based on GC (Garbage Collection, Reference), invalidation of values is hard to estimate. Even if a value hasn't exceeded the expiration, it's still possible to not be retrieved.

    Default implementation will call cleanUp() before end of each other method calling to clean up expired data. This means that expired data may still occupy memory until the next invocation of cleanUp(). Scheduling task for cleanUp() can effectively resolve this problem.

    GekCache.RemoveListener is used to listen removing action of ths cache. As mentioned above, if a value is cleared by GC before GekCache.RemoveListener.onRemove(Object, Object, GekCache) is called, the value parameter will be passed to null.

      • get

        @Nullable
V get(K key,
                 java.util.function.Function<? super K,? extends V> loader)
        Returns value associating with specified key, and it performs like ConcurrentHashMap.computeIfAbsent(Object, Function):

        If the specified key is not already associated with a value, attempts to compute its value using the given loader and enters it into this cache. Null is permitted so the null value will also be entered.

        This cache is thread-safe so the loader function is applied at most once per key, and blocks other thread.

        This is a compute operation if the computation is occurred, otherwise this is a get operation.

        Parameters:
        key - specified key
        loader - given loader
        Returns:
        value associating with specified key, may be computed from given loader

      • getOptional

        @Nullable
@Nullable java.util.Optional<V> getOptional(K key,
                                                       java.util.function.Function<? super K,GekCache.Value<? extends V>> loader)
        Returns value wrapped by Optional associating with specified key, and it performs like ConcurrentHashMap.computeIfAbsent(Object, Function):

        If the specified key is not already associated with a value, attempts to compute its value as GekCache.Value using the given loader and enters it into this cache. If the loader returns null, no mapping will be recorded and this method will return null.

        This cache is thread-safe so the loader function is applied at most once per key, and blocks other thread.

        This is a compute operation if the computation is occurred, otherwise this is a get operation.

        Parameters:
        key - specified key
        loader - given loader
        Returns:
        value associating with specified key, may be computed from given loader
